In a world where everyone has something to say and no one thinks they are wrong, set an example of self-restraint and Godly speech. Choose your words carefully. Speak life! Speak love! Speak joy and peace and hope! And of course, speak Truth! However, choosing the right words is just as important at choosing the right time. Pay attention to how and where you speak -- the time is not always ripe and the listener not always receptive or ready. The right words at the right time give life.  Don't rush things in order to be heard. Rushed words only add to the noise. Be patient and at the right time your words will be heard.

|❇| "I'll keep you safe"
your words crossing my heart
over and over again
providing depth 
to the pangs of separation
and the crushing of my belief
that you were the one
I thought so
now I know
what you were to me
just another dark cloud 
that didn't rain
on my barren land
showed me dreams 
of lush greens and lilies
and disappeared 
maybe to another land 
a land less barren than mine |❇| _______________________________________________

When the girl got off the train at the college town,
she leapt up and wrapped her legs around the waist
of the boy she’d come to visit, and they spun
around, embracing and shrieking with joy.
Their love set off a piccolo’s vibration.
Those years are gone for us—I see you every day,
we eat meals together from decades-old plates.
But when we lie in bed at night, you take my hand,
and I feel the orb that’s formed around us tighten,
while you and I, like knitting needles in a ball
of yarn, lie beside each other, fingers touching.
